    "summary": "I have a long experience as a System Engineer and IT Technical Support Engineer. \nIn the last years I have been focusing on the Support role handling complex cases from customer all over the World. I am working with Nutanix technology but I have to deal with several other software vendors (Microsoft, VMware, Veeam, CommVault, HYCU, etc.)\nI also have experience in managing datacenters with VMware Virtual Infrastructure. I have deep knowledge in managing different Operating Systems with all their features: Windows Server and Client from 2003 to 2019 edition, Linux in different edition, FreeBSD, Active Directory, DNS, DHCP, DFS, IIS. \nI also installed, configured and managed software for cloud services: Exchange or Linux email, Windows RemoteApp, Veeam Backup&Replication, MS SQL and file sync and share services. I have experience in IT Project Management, designing and implementing complete physical and virtual infrastructures on the customers\u2019 site using Nutanix, VMware or HyperV technology. I\u2019m able to configure hosts (Nutanix, DELL, HP, IBM), storage (Nutanix, DELL, Synology, Fujitsu, Iomega, NetApp), switches (Cisco), routers (Cisco), firewalls (Cisco ASA, Sonicwall, pfSense). I have experience with Powershell and Bash scripts and with monitoring appliance.\nI am a person who pays great attention to the relationship with the customers and works hard. I also appreciate working in a collaborative environment with other team members. I have excellent documentation, communication and interpersonal skills, with an ability to liaise effectively and professionally with individuals at all levels. I have been in a managerial position for many years and I believe my greatest assets are my ability to work with different personalities and adapt quickly to different situations. A solid academic background in computer science and the curiosity for the evolution of the Information and Communication Technologies push me to keep constantly updated. Therefore I have followed some professional courses on the technologies I use in my daily job.",
